 　Professor of History at Yale University, majoring in modern Eastern European history, graduated from Oxford University. In a very short period of time, Timothy Schneider teaches us how to respond to the current situation and create a better future. It is important to find out the key points in the accumulation of time. When things are not happening, you should smell the warnings based on past experience and avoid repeating the same mistakes.<br />
